headline: Gemini Falls Further Below IPO Price. Crypto Stocks Are Fading Fast.
summary: It might not be another crypto winter just yet.  Just look at  Gemini Space Station  the crypto investment firm led by Cameron and Tyler Winklevoss that recently went public.  When it debuted on Sept. 12, the stock surged 45% in the first few minutes of trading and finished with a gain of almost 15% from its initial public offering price.

headline: Robinhood, AppLovin, EMCOR joining S&P 500. What does EMCOR do?
summary: Robinhood (HOOD), AppLovin (APP), and EMCOR (EME) are joining the S&P 500 (^GSPC) on Monday, Sept. 22 as part of the index's quarterly rebalancing. While Robinhood and AppLovin are likely to be familiar names among investors, EMCOR may be less well-known. Julie Hyman outlines what EMCOR does.
